properties.name: Deer Creek Loop
properties.description: This ride includes a long, 12 mile, climb and some wonderful views. Start and end in the Aspen Grove Shopping Center which has plenty of parking and a bike shop for any last minute needs.

properties.name: Morrison to Lookout Mountain
properties.description: This out & back route starts with a gradual climb from Morrison to Golden, then a tough 5 mile climb to the top of Lookout Mountain. On the way up you'll enjoy great views of Golden and the skyline of Denver. Once at the top, you can visit Buffalo Bill's grave or just replenish your water supply at the general store.

properties.name: Littleton to REI Flagship - Downtown Denver
properties.description: This is an easy out & back route that starts from a small shopping Center in Littleton (with a bike shop for convenience). The entire route is very flat and is on a dedicated bike path so those new to cycling should have no fear of vehicular traffic. Once downtown, do some shopping at REI or grab a coffee at Starbucks on the first floor and head back to Littleton.
